fields.description:
When enabling employees for remittances we typically get employee ID or person ID together with the company ID. What we have seen in the past is that there’s duplicate profile so that the person given to us is actually not a cardholder. 

Expectations: Any person in the CSV file should be a cardholder. Any person in the CSV file that is NOT a cardholder is indication of an error that needs to be followed up by [~accountid:5e78fdd1dde7030c4f0d3ddd]  / CS with the farm. 

AC: Update the Remittance bulk enablement script so that people add up to these categories. 
Exists: 1. have a card and is already enabled. →  no change
Exists: 2. have a card and is not enabled for ECG →  save who they are, and update them for remittance. 
*New 3. does not have a card → save who they are and notify* [~accountid:5e78fdd1dde7030c4f0d3ddd] *about them.*

comments.body:
task. Use the script and parse from CSV .
create a CSV file where some employee IDs are NOT cardholders. 
The script should detect this and spit out a CSV file with “employeeIDs_unable_to_convert_for_remittances.csv” or similar. 

comment out, or run in “read-only-mode” to make sure we aren’t turning on remittances for someone by accident. 

OR – wait until we should enable someone for remittances and do this in “bulk” for one person, + the ones that should fail.

comments.body: [~accountid:5e78fdd1dde7030c4f0d3ddd]  it seems that 10 of these 40 people do not have paycards yet.

Can we get the names or IDs?

[~accountid:618067a4b9c549006f45c3ac] for 👀

[~accountid:5e78fdd1dde7030c4f0d3ddd]  AFAIK only one. person was new. 

Juan Carlos,Guzman Melgoza,

CH id: yeDXcf_Y7HiidkgQVEgx4

He’s now enabled.

Hi [~accountid:613e6eaa1238e8007108f513] 

I’m checkin, according Tableau these CHs aren’t  _remittances_eligible,_ the value is FALSE

{noformat}JuRO5ETQ38OFLtm7jU4me

nGEabo4hdipr6yff_DNUo

jOEPWn7haXgkpLKMa4Q2q

yeDXcf_Y7HiidkgQVEgx4 
{noformat}

Remittances_eligible status is important because it is the data that I take to send drip messages related remittances, if someone is enabled and the status is FALSE, I cannot know that person has the feature. 

I see *JuRO5ETQ38OFLtm7jU4me* was able to make a transfer, so he is enabled

!Captura de Pantalla 2023-06-02 a la(s) 17.33.07.png|width=1258,height=123!

But, How this manual enabling process  reflect the info in our database that feeds Tableau? [~accountid:5fc6cab5dd0c59007539be49] for 👀

[~accountid:5e78fdd1dde7030c4f0d3ddd] 

{{JuRO5ETQ38OFLtm7jU4me }} - Jose Elias,Salas Llamas (/)  no change, was enabled earlier. 
{{yeDXcf_Y7HiidkgQVEgx4 - Juan Carlos,Guzman Melgoza}}, no change, was enabled in this ticket

🔴  {{nGEabo4hdipr6yff_DNUo - Juan Daniel,Mendoza Mendoza, employee_id: 1769, pers.id:558360}} . Juan Daniel was not enabled as the CSV file with employee ID was not accurate for him. The file says his employee ID was 2621 but it’s 1769. 

There’s another “Juan Daniel,Mendoza Mendoza, employee_id: 2621” who is NOT a cardholder. Due to this mismatch the bulk enabling script did not enable the person.  Please ask the company to find out if `{{Juan Daniel,Mendoza Mendoza, employee_id: 1769,}} is H2A and then we can enable him. 
 
🔴 {{jOEPWn7haXgkpLKMa4Q2q Juan Jose,Pablo Gatica  pers.id: 558332  has employee_id: 1777.}}  The file says that the employee id is 2633  

employee_id 2633 also goes to a Juan Jose,Pablo Gatica. this person is not a cardholder. 
Due to this mismatch the bulk enabling script did not enable the person.  Please ask the company to find out if `{{Juan Jose,Pablo Gatica  pers.id: 558332  employee_id: 1777,}} is H2A and then we can enable him.

[~accountid:62780ad493111000689ece08]  i.e. see below. The script worked. 
Maybe we should add some error output for H2As that are not with the correct information

Thank you [~accountid:613e6eaa1238e8007108f513] I see these CHs have duplicated Employee IDs. Is the employee ID the information the script looks for and takes to enable a CH?

!Captura de Pantalla 2023-06-05 a la(s) 16.12.18.png|width=1365,height=282!

!Captura de Pantalla 2023-06-05 a la(s) 16.13.00.png|width=1350,height=470!

We can either look at {{employee_id}} or we can use {{person_id}}. Of course we can modify the script to be whatever, in case we have a need to rather use whatever comes from the client. 

In the past the bulk enabling CSVs has come with this data. 
So in this case the company screwed something up and they provided the wrong employee_id to us, the provided employee_id weren’t card holders and so the script didn’t work for them. 

it does give me pause, at this point, should we have them clarify their data? Or should we “assume, and just do it”? 
personally, I prefer to know  that we aren’t enabling remittances for the wrong person, and that’s why didn’t enable them yet. 

We can adjust this approach of course, happy for your feedback on this. It’s a tricky balance between being “thorough” and “nitpicking”

Ok [~accountid:613e6eaa1238e8007108f513] , If you add an error and then let me know those cases, I could crossmatch the info from the client site (Download Paycard Only de Blue River) In this case I see both CH's names.

!Captura de Pantalla 2023-06-05 a la(s) 16.30.24.png|width=632,height=359!

If we want to be proactive and accurate, I could add previous steps:

1.- Download Paycard Only de Blue River
2.- Crossmatch with the H2A file received from the client
3.- If the name matches, we can enable them
4.- Make the Jira Ticket to enable H2A’s matches

What do you think?

I think that’s a good idea moving forward. 

I will see if I can improve our script. Essentially if there is a mismatch as we saw in this ticket then we need to generate these misses into a CSV file and can follow up with you. 

Do you need anything else than what we have so far, for this ticket to be completed? [~accountid:5e78fdd1dde7030c4f0d3ddd] ?
It’s ok [~accountid:613e6eaa1238e8007108f513] please go ahead and close this ticket.

[~accountid:613e6eaa1238e8007108f513] Could you please help me enabling remittances for 

*Juan Jose Pablo Gatica -  CHID: jOEPWn7haXgkpLKMa4Q2q*

*Juan Daniel Mendoza - CHID: nGEabo4hdipr6yff_DNUo*

They are in this list with duplicated EID, so the script didn't found as cardholders. According to Qolo those are their CHID.
[~accountid:5e78fdd1dde7030c4f0d3ddd]  it’s taken care of for both of the cardholders now
FYI [~accountid:619f24d9ef18ca00712cc620]
Thank you both!
